1 infl icting serious bodily injury, except for a weapon carried for
2 lawful self-defense in compliance under the Oklahoma Self Defense
3 Self-Defense Act;
4 4. “Passenger” means any person served by the bus
5 transportation company; and
6 5. “Rolling stock transit vehicles” include buses, vans, cars,
7 railcars, locomotives, trolley cars, ferry boats, and vehicles used
8 for support services;
9 6. “Terminal” means a bus station, stop, platform, or depot or
10 any facility operated or leased by or operated on behalf of a bus
11 transportation company. This term shall include a reasonable area
12 immediately adjacent to any designated stop along the route traveled
13 by any bus rolling stock transit vehicle operated by a bus
14 transportation company and parking lots or parking areas adjacent to
15 a terminal; and
16 7. “Transit worker” means any employee, contractor, or
17 volunteer working on behalf of a transit agency.
18 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 1903, is
19 amended to read as follows:
20 Section 1903. A. No person shall by force or violence, or
21 threat of force or violence, seize or exercise control of any bus
22 rolling stock transit vehicle. Any person violating this subsection
23 shall be guilty of a felony and shall, upon conviction, be punished
24 by imprisonment in the custody of the Department of Corrections for
ENGR. S. B. NO. 562 Page 2

1 not more than twenty (20) years, or by a fine of not more than
2 Twenty Thousand Dollars ($20,000.00), or by both such fine and
3 imprisonment.
4 B. In addition, no No person shall intimidate, threaten,
5 assault, or batter any driver, attendant, guard, transit worker, or
6 passenger of any bus with intent to violate subsection A of this
7 section rolling stock transit vehicle or cause disruption to the
8 provided service or cause harm to any person. Any person violating
9 this subsection shall be guilty of a felony and shall, upon
10 conviction, be punished by imprisonment in the custody of the
11 Department of Corrections for not more than ten (10) years, or by a
12 fine of not more than Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00), or by both
13 such fine and imprisonment.
14 C. In addition, any Any person violating subsection A or B of
15 this section using a dangerous or deadly weapon shall be guilty of a
16 felony, and shall, upon conviction, be punished by imprisonment in
17 the custody of the Department of Corrections for not more than
18 twenty (20) years, or by a fine of not more than Twenty Thousand
19 Dollars ($20,000.00), or by both such fine and imprisonment.
20 D. It shall be unlawful for any person to discharge any firearm
21 into or within any bus rolling stock transit vehicle, terminal, or
22 other transportation facility, unless such action is determined to
23 have been in defensive force resulting from reasonable fear of
24 imminent peril of death or great bodily harm to himself or herself
